{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1000,"text":"I've been fascinated with crop diversity for about 35 years from now,"},{"time":5000,"text":"ever since I stumbled across a fairly obscure academic article"},{"time":10000,"text":"by a guy named Jack Harlan."},{"time":12000,"text":"And he described the diversity within crops --"},{"time":15000,"text":"all the different kinds of wheat and rice and such --"},{"time":18000,"text":"as a genetic resource."},{"time":20000,"text":"And he said, \"This genetic resource,\" --"},{"time":23000,"text":"and I'll never forget the words --"},{"time":25000,"text":"\"stands between us and catastrophic starvation"},{"time":28000,"text":"on a scale we cannot imagine.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":31000,"text":"I figured he was either really on to something,"},{"time":34000,"text":"or he was one of these academic nutcases."},{"time":36000,"text":"So, I looked a little further,"},{"time":38000,"text":"and what I figured out was that he wasn't a nutcase."},{"time":41000,"text":"He was the most respected scientist in the field."},{"time":45000,"text":"What he understood was that biological diversity -- crop diversity --"},{"time":51000,"text":"is the biological foundation of agriculture."},{"time":54000,"text":"It's the raw material, the stuff, of evolution in our agricultural crops."},{"time":59000,"text":"Not a trivial matter."},{"time":61000,"text":"And he also understood that that foundation was crumbling,"},{"time":66000,"text":"literally crumbling."},{"time":68000,"text":"That indeed, a mass extinction was underway"},{"time":72000,"text":"in our fields, in our agricultural system."},{"time":76000,"text":"And that this mass extinction was taking place"},{"time":79000,"text":"with very few people noticing"},{"time":81000,"text":"and even fewer caring."}]},{"cues":[{"time":84000,"text":"Now, I know that many of you don't stop"},{"time":86000,"text":"to think about diversity in agricultural systems"},{"time":89000,"text":"and, let's face it, that's logical."},{"time":91000,"text":"You don't see it in the newspaper every day."},{"time":94000,"text":"And when you go into the supermarket, you certainly don't see a lot of choices there."},{"time":97000,"text":"You see apples that are red, yellow, and green and that's about it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":102000,"text":"So, let me show you a picture of one form of diversity."},{"time":106000,"text":"Here's some beans,"},{"time":108000,"text":"and there are about 35 or 40 different"},{"time":112000,"text":"varieties of beans on this picture."},{"time":116000,"text":"Now, imagine each one of these varieties as being distinct from another"},{"time":120000,"text":"about the same way as a poodle from a Great Dane."},{"time":122000,"text":"If I wanted to show you a picture of all the dog breeds in the world,"},{"time":127000,"text":"and I put 30 or 40 of them on a slide, it would take about 10 slides"},{"time":131000,"text":"because there about 400 breeds of dogs in the world."},{"time":135000,"text":"But there are 35 to 40,000 different varieties of beans."},{"time":139000,"text":"So if I were to going to show you all the beans in the world,"},{"time":142000,"text":"and I had a slide like this, and I switched it every second,"},{"time":146000,"text":"it would take up my entire TED talk,"},{"time":148000,"text":"and I wouldn't have to say anything."}]},{"cues":[{"time":152000,"text":"But the interesting thing is that this diversity -- and the tragic thing is --"},{"time":157000,"text":"that this diversity is being lost."},{"time":160000,"text":"We have about 200,000 different varieties of wheat,"},{"time":164000,"text":"and we have about 2 to 400,000 different varieties of rice,"},{"time":169000,"text":"but it's being lost."},{"time":171000,"text":"And I want to give you an example of that."},{"time":173000,"text":"It's a bit of a personal example, in fact."},{"time":175000,"text":"In the United States, in the 1800s -- that's where we have the best data --"},{"time":180000,"text":"farmers and gardeners were growing 7,100"},{"time":185000,"text":"named varieties of apples."},{"time":188000,"text":"Imagine that. 7,100 apples with names."},{"time":192000,"text":"Today, 6,800 of those are extinct,"},{"time":197000,"text":"no longer to be seen again."}]},{"cues":[{"time":200000,"text":"I used to have a list of these extinct apples,"},{"time":202000,"text":"and when I would go out and give a presentation,"},{"time":204000,"text":"I would pass the list out in the audience."},{"time":206000,"text":"I wouldn't tell them what it was, but it was in alphabetical order,"},{"time":209000,"text":"and I would tell them to look for their names, their family names,"},{"time":212000,"text":"their mother's maiden name."},{"time":214000,"text":"And at the end of the speech, I would ask, \"How many people have found a name?\""},{"time":218000,"text":"And I never had fewer than two-thirds of an audience hold up their hand."},{"time":223000,"text":"And I said, \"You know what? These apples come from your ancestors,"},{"time":229000,"text":"and your ancestors gave them the greatest honor they could give them."},{"time":234000,"text":"They gave them their name."},{"time":237000,"text":"The bad news is they're extinct."},{"time":239000,"text":"The good news is a third of you didn't hold up your hand. Your apple's still out there."},{"time":244000,"text":"Find it. Make sure it doesn't join the list.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":249000,"text":"So, I want to tell you that the piece of the good news is"},{"time":252000,"text":"that the Fowler apple is still out there."},{"time":257000,"text":"And there's an old book back here,"},{"time":259000,"text":"and I want to read a piece from it."},{"time":266000,"text":"This book was published in 1904."},{"time":269000,"text":"It's called \"The Apples of New York\" and this is the second volume."},{"time":272000,"text":"See, we used to have a lot of apples."},{"time":275000,"text":"And the Fowler apple is described in here --"},{"time":279000,"text":"I hope this doesn't surprise you --"},{"time":283000,"text":"as, \"a beautiful fruit.\""},{"time":285000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":291000,"text":"I don't know if we named the apple or if the apple named us, but ..."},{"time":295000,"text":"but, to be honest, the description goes on"},{"time":299000,"text":"and it says that it \"doesn't rank high in quality, however.\""},{"time":303000,"text":"And then he has to go even further."},{"time":305000,"text":"It sounds like it was written by an old school teacher of mine."},{"time":308000,"text":"\"As grown in New York, the fruit usually fails to develop properly in size and quality"},{"time":314000,"text":"and is, on the whole, unsatisfactory.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":316000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":324000,"text":"And I guess there's a lesson to be learned here,"},{"time":326000,"text":"and the lesson is: so why save it?"},{"time":329000,"text":"I get this question all the time. Why don't we just save the best one?"},{"time":333000,"text":"And there are a couple of answers to that question."},{"time":335000,"text":"One thing is that there is no such thing as a best one."},{"time":339000,"text":"Today's best variety is tomorrow's lunch for insects or pests or disease."},{"time":344000,"text":"The other thing is that maybe that Fowler apple"},{"time":347000,"text":"or maybe a variety of wheat that's not economical right now"},{"time":352000,"text":"has disease or pest resistance"},{"time":354000,"text":"or some quality that we're going to need for climate change that the others don't."},{"time":358000,"text":"So it's not necessary, thank God,"},{"time":362000,"text":"that the Fowler apple is the best apple in the world."},{"time":365000,"text":"It's just necessary or interesting that it might have one good, unique trait."},{"time":371000,"text":"And for that reason, we ought to be saving it."},{"time":374000,"text":"Why? As a raw material, as a trait we can use in the future."},{"time":380000,"text":"Think of diversity as giving us options."},{"time":388000,"text":"And options, of course, are exactly what we need in an era of climate change."}]},{"cues":[{"time":395000,"text":"I want to show you two slides,"},{"time":397000,"text":"but first, I want to tell you that we've been working at the Global Crop Diversity Trust"},{"time":401000,"text":"with a number of scientists -- particularly at Stanford and University of Washington --"},{"time":405000,"text":"to ask the question: What's going to happen to agriculture in an era of climate change"},{"time":409000,"text":"and what kind of traits and characteristics do we need in our agricultural crops"},{"time":413000,"text":"to be able to adapt to this?"},{"time":416000,"text":"In short, the answer is that in the future, in many countries,"},{"time":420000,"text":"the coldest growing seasons are going to be hotter"},{"time":424000,"text":"than anything those crops have seen in the past."},{"time":427000,"text":"The coldest growing seasons of the future,"},{"time":430000,"text":"hotter than the hottest of the past."},{"time":433000,"text":"Is agriculture adapted to that?"},{"time":435000,"text":"I don't know. Can fish play the piano?"},{"time":438000,"text":"If agriculture hasn't experienced that, how could it be adapted?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":443000,"text":"Now, the highest concentration of poor and hungry people in the world,"},{"time":447000,"text":"and the place where climate change, ironically, is going to be the worst"},{"time":450000,"text":"is in South Asia and sub-Saharan Africa."},{"time":453000,"text":"So I've picked two examples here, and I want to show you."},{"time":456000,"text":"In the histogram before you now,"},{"time":458000,"text":"the blue bars represent the historical range of temperatures,"},{"time":462000,"text":"going back about far as we have temperature data."},{"time":464000,"text":"And you can see that there's some difference"},{"time":467000,"text":"between one growing season and another."},{"time":469000,"text":"Some are colder, some are hotter and it's a bell shaped curve."},{"time":472000,"text":"The tallest bar is the average temperature for the most number of growing seasons."},{"time":478000,"text":"In the future, later this century, it's going to look like the red,"},{"time":482000,"text":"totally out of bounds."},{"time":484000,"text":"The agricultural system and, more importantly, the crops in the field in India"},{"time":488000,"text":"have never experienced this before."}]},{"cues":[{"time":491000,"text":"Here's South Africa. The same story."},{"time":495000,"text":"But the most interesting thing about South Africa is"},{"time":497000,"text":"we don't have to wait for 2070 for there to be trouble."},{"time":501000,"text":"By 2030, if the maize, or corn, varieties, which is the dominant crop --"},{"time":505000,"text":"50 percent of the nutrition in Southern Africa are still in the field --"},{"time":509000,"text":"in 2030, we'll have a 30 percent decrease in production of maize"},{"time":514000,"text":"because of the climate change already in 2030."},{"time":518000,"text":"30 percent decrease of production in the context of increasing population,"},{"time":522000,"text":"that's a food crisis. It's global in nature."},{"time":525000,"text":"We will watch children starve to death on TV."},{"time":528000,"text":"Now, you may say that 20 years is a long way off."},{"time":531000,"text":"It's two breeding cycles for maize."},{"time":533000,"text":"We have two rolls of the dice to get this right."},{"time":536000,"text":"We have to get climate-ready crops in the field,"},{"time":539000,"text":"and we have to do that rather quickly."}]},{"cues":[{"time":543000,"text":"Now, the good news is that we have conserved."},{"time":546000,"text":"We have collected and conserved a great deal of biological diversity,"},{"time":548000,"text":"agricultural diversity, mostly in the form of seed,"},{"time":552000,"text":"and we put it in seed banks, which is a fancy way of saying a freezer."},{"time":557000,"text":"If you want to conserve seed for a long term"},{"time":560000,"text":"and you want to make it available to plant breeders and researchers,"},{"time":563000,"text":"you dry it and then you freeze it."},{"time":566000,"text":"Unfortunately, these seed banks are located around the world in buildings"},{"time":569000,"text":"and they're vulnerable."},{"time":571000,"text":"Disasters have happened. In recent years we lost the gene bank,"},{"time":574000,"text":"the seed bank in Iraq and Afghanistan. You can guess why."},{"time":578000,"text":"In Rwanda, in the Solomon Islands."},{"time":580000,"text":"And then there are just daily disasters that take place in these buildings,"},{"time":583000,"text":"financial problems and mismanagement and equipment failures,"},{"time":587000,"text":"and all kinds of things, and every time something like this happens,"},{"time":590000,"text":"it means extinction. We lose diversity."},{"time":593000,"text":"And I'm not talking about losing diversity in the same way that you lose your car keys."},{"time":598000,"text":"I'm talking about losing it in the same way that we lost the dinosaurs:"},{"time":602000,"text":"actually losing it, never to be seen again."}]},{"cues":[{"time":604000,"text":"So, a number of us got together and decided that, you know, enough is enough"},{"time":608000,"text":"and we need to do something about that and we need to have a facility"},{"time":612000,"text":"that can really offer protection for our biological diversity of --"},{"time":617000,"text":"maybe not the most charismatic diversity."},{"time":619000,"text":"You don't look in the eyes of a carrot seed quite in the way you do a panda bear,"},{"time":625000,"text":"but it's very important diversity."},{"time":628000,"text":"So we needed a really safe place, and we went quite far north to find it."},{"time":637000,"text":"To Svalbard, in fact."},{"time":639000,"text":"This is above mainland Norway. You can see Greenland there."},{"time":642000,"text":"That's at 78 degrees north."},{"time":644000,"text":"It's as far as you can fly on a regularly scheduled airplane."},{"time":649000,"text":"It's a remarkably beautiful landscape. I can't even begin to describe it to you."},{"time":653000,"text":"It's otherworldly, beautiful."},{"time":655000,"text":"We worked with the Norwegian government"},{"time":658000,"text":"and with the NorGen, the Norwegian Genetic Resources Program,"},{"time":662000,"text":"to design this facility."},{"time":664000,"text":"What you see is an artist's conception of this facility,"},{"time":667000,"text":"which is built in a mountain in Svalbard."},{"time":670000,"text":"The idea of Svalbard was that it's cold,"},{"time":673000,"text":"so we get natural freezing temperatures."},{"time":676000,"text":"But it's remote. It's remote and accessible"},{"time":680000,"text":"so it's safe and we don't depend on mechanical refrigeration."}]},{"cues":[{"time":685000,"text":"This is more than just an artist's dream, it's now a reality."},{"time":691000,"text":"And this next picture shows it in context, in Svalbard."},{"time":696000,"text":"And here's the front door of this facility."},{"time":701000,"text":"When you open up the front door,"},{"time":704000,"text":"this is what you're looking at. It's pretty simple. It's a hole in the ground."},{"time":707000,"text":"It's a tunnel, and you go into the tunnel,"},{"time":710000,"text":"chiseled in solid rock, about 130 meters."},{"time":713000,"text":"There are now a couple of security doors, so you won't see it quite like this."},{"time":717000,"text":"Again, when you get to the back, you get into an area that's really my favorite place."},{"time":722000,"text":"I think of it as sort of a cathedral."},{"time":724000,"text":"And I know that this tags me as a bit of a nerd, but ..."},{"time":728000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":731000,"text":"Some of the happiest days of my life have been spent ..."},{"time":734000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":736000,"text":"in this place there."}]},{"cues":[{"time":738000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":744000,"text":"If you were to walk into one of these rooms, you would see this."},{"time":752000,"text":"It's not very exciting, but if you know what's there, it's pretty emotional."},{"time":757000,"text":"We have now about 425,000"},{"time":761000,"text":"samples of unique crop varieties."},{"time":765000,"text":"There's 70,000 samples of different varieties of rice"},{"time":769000,"text":"in this facility right now."},{"time":772000,"text":"About a year from now, we'll have over half a million samples."},{"time":775000,"text":"We're going up to over a million, and someday we'll basically have samples --"},{"time":779000,"text":"about 500 seeds --"},{"time":781000,"text":"of every variety of agricultural crop that can be stored in a frozen state"},{"time":786000,"text":"in this facility."},{"time":788000,"text":"This is a backup system for world agriculture."},{"time":791000,"text":"It's a backup system for all the seed banks. Storage is free."},{"time":795000,"text":"It operates like a safety deposit box."},{"time":798000,"text":"Norway owns the mountain and the facility, but the depositors own the seed."},{"time":804000,"text":"And if anything happens, then they can come back and get it."},{"time":808000,"text":"This particular picture that you see shows the national collection of the United States,"},{"time":812000,"text":"of Canada, and an international institution from Syria."}]},{"cues":[{"time":816000,"text":"I think it's interesting in that this facility, I think,"},{"time":820000,"text":"is almost the only thing I can think of these days where countries,"},{"time":824000,"text":"literally, every country in the world --"},{"time":827000,"text":"because we have seeds from every country in the world --"},{"time":829000,"text":"all the countries of the world have gotten together"},{"time":832000,"text":"to do something that's both long term, sustainable and positive."},{"time":838000,"text":"I can't think of anything else that's happened in my lifetime that way."}]},{"cues":[{"time":841000,"text":"I can't look you in the eyes and tell you that I have a solution"},{"time":846000,"text":"for climate change, for the water crisis."},{"time":851000,"text":"Agriculture takes 70 percent of fresh water supplies on earth."},{"time":855000,"text":"I can't look you in the eyes and tell you that there is such a solution"},{"time":858000,"text":"for those things, or the energy crisis, or world hunger, or peace in conflict."},{"time":863000,"text":"I can't look you in the eyes and tell you that I have a simple solution for that,"},{"time":866000,"text":"but I can look you in the eyes and tell you that we can't solve any of those problems"},{"time":872000,"text":"if we don't have crop diversity."},{"time":874000,"text":"Because I challenge you to think of an effective, efficient, sustainable"},{"time":882000,"text":"solution to climate change if we don't have crop diversity."},{"time":886000,"text":"Because, quite literally, if agriculture doesn't adapt to climate change,"},{"time":892000,"text":"neither will we."},{"time":894000,"text":"And if crops don't adapt to climate change, neither will agriculture,"},{"time":899000,"text":"neither will we."}]},{"cues":[{"time":901000,"text":"So, this is not something pretty and nice to do."},{"time":904000,"text":"There are a lot of people who would love to have this diversity exist"},{"time":907000,"text":"just for the existence value of it."},{"time":909000,"text":"It is, I agree, a nice thing to do."},{"time":912000,"text":"But it's a necessary thing to do."},{"time":914000,"text":"So, in a very real sense, I believe that we, as an international community,"},{"time":920000,"text":"should get organized to complete the task."},{"time":923000,"text":"The Svalbard Global Seed Vault is a wonderful gift"},{"time":926000,"text":"that Norway and others have given us,"},{"time":928000,"text":"but it's not the complete answer."},{"time":930000,"text":"We need to collect the remaining diversity that's out there."},{"time":933000,"text":"We need to put it into good seed banks"},{"time":936000,"text":"that can offer those seeds to researchers in the future."},{"time":940000,"text":"We need to catalog it. It's a library of life,"},{"time":942000,"text":"but right now I would say we don't have a card catalog for it."},{"time":946000,"text":"And we need to support it financially."}]},{"cues":[{"time":949000,"text":"My big idea would be that while we think of it as commonplace"},{"time":954000,"text":"to endow an art museum or endow a chair at a university,"},{"time":959000,"text":"we really ought to be thinking about endowing wheat."},{"time":963000,"text":"30 million dollars in an endowment would take care"},{"time":967000,"text":"of preserving all the diversity in wheat forever."},{"time":971000,"text":"So we need to be thinking a little bit in those terms."}]},{"cues":[{"time":974000,"text":"And my final thought is that we, of course, by conserving wheat,"},{"time":982000,"text":"rice, potatoes, and the other crops,"},{"time":985000,"text":"we may, quite simply, end up saving ourselves."}]},{"cues":[{"time":989000,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":991000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}